{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "This resonates well with the general assertion that the quality of decisions by human-AI systems depends crucially on the human expertise within such systems (Ninaus & Sailer, 2022).",
    "However, both the development and preservation of expertise require practicing domain-specific problem-solving capabilities (Elvira et al., 2017; Tynjälä, 2008; Tynjälä et al., 2006).",
    "As novices advance from easier to more difficult problems, they continuously engage in three learning processes.",
    "First, they transform conceptual knowledge into experiential knowledge when, for instance, applying general concepts to specific problems in particular contexts.",
    "Second, they also need to explicate experiential into conceptual knowledge to, for instance, make tacit knowledge (Patterson et al., 2010) accessible to other people as well as to metacognitive processes like reflection."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "This resonates well with the general assertion that the quality of decisions by human-AI systems depends crucially on the human expertise within such systems (Ninaus & Sailer, 2022).",
    "However, both the development and preservation of expertise require practicing domain-specific problem-solving capabilities (Elvira et al., 2017; Tynjälä, 2008; Tynjälä et al., 2006).",
    "Second, they also need to explicate experiential into conceptual knowledge to, for instance, make tacit knowledge (Patterson et al., 2010) accessible to other people as well as to metacognitive processes like reflection."
  ]
